title: One Page CV
text:
I am a fourth-year Software Engineering student at Pontificia Universidad Católica de Chile. I am passionate about creating authentic and real social networking environments, focusing on genuine interactions and combating the negative effects of social pressure and the quest for perfection in traditional social media.






Degree: Software Engineering
Year: Fourth Year








Role: Lead Developer
Description: Developing a unique social network where users’ profiles are shaped by comments from their friends, fostering more authentic interactions.
Technologies Used: React, PostgreSQL, Node.js, Koa.js, Sequelize





Role: Founder
Description: Home decor business focusing on creating cozy and welcoming spaces.





Role: Founder
Description: Mindfulness and yoga workshops aimed at improving mental health and well-being.






Programming Languages: JavaScript, Python, SQL
Frameworks and Libraries: React, Node.js, Koa.js, Sequelize
Tools: Git, GitHub
